{"questionId":"23191","questionHtml":"<p>Two wires, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>X</mtext></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>Y</mtext></math>, are made of the same material and have equal length. The diameter&nbsp;of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>X</mtext></math> is twice that of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>Y</mtext></math>.</p>\n<p>What is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mtext>resistance&nbsp;of&nbsp;X</mtext><mtext>resistance&nbsp;of&nbsp;Y</mtext></mfrac></math>?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp; <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>4</mn></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>A</p>","meta":{"questionId":"23191","referenceCode":"21N.1.SL.TZ0.19","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"Two wires, X and Y, are made of the same material and have equal length. The diameter of X is twice that of Y. What is resistance of Xresistance of Y? A. 14 B. 12 C. 2 D. 4","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"19","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism","5.2 – Heating effect of electric currents","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}